---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About EES | CEC Accredited Solar & Energy Installer Geelong"
  description="EES is a CEC-accredited solar and energy services company in Geelong, specialising in solar, batteries, heat pumps, hydronic heating, and home automation."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About EES</h1>
      <p>Local energy experts based in Geelong.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        Environmental Energy Services (EES) is a Geelong-based energy company that designs, installs, and supports complete home and commercial energy systems — solar, batteries, heat pumps, hydronic heating and cooling, and smart automation.
      </p>
      <p>
        We're not just a solar installer. We take a whole-of-home approach to energy, designing systems where every component works together — not in isolation. Our goal is to reduce your energy costs, improve your comfort, and move your property toward energy independence.
      </p>

      <h2>What Makes Us Different</h2>
      <p>
        Most solar companies sell panels and inverters. We design integrated energy systems.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>We build and test our own products</strong> — our hydronic ceiling panels and Environmental Service Pod are designed, manufactured, and tested in-house at our purpose-built <a href="/laboratory/facility">research facility</a> in Geelong</li>
        <li><strong>We do the research</strong> — our TestCell is built to ASHRAE-55 and ISO 7730 standards for real-world thermal comfort and energy efficiency testing</li>
        <li><strong>We install what we design</strong> — our CEC-accredited electricians install every system. No subcontractors, no third-party handoffs</li>
        <li><strong>We commission and test every system</strong> — we walk you through the monitoring and make sure everything is working correctly before we leave</li>
        <li><strong>We support long-term</strong> — every installation comes with a <strong>10-year workmanship warranty</strong> and ongoing local support</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Accreditations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>CEC Accredited Installer</strong> — Clean Energy Council accreditation for solar design and installation</li>
        <li><strong>Solar Victoria Approved Retailer</strong> — authorised to process Victorian Government solar and battery rebates</li>
        <li><strong>SAI Approved Retailer</strong> — Solar Accreditation Initiative approved</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Services</h2>
      <p>
        We provide the full range of energy services for homes and businesses:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/services/residential/solar-systems">Solar panel systems</a> — residential and commercial</li>
        <li><a href="/services/residential/battery-systems">Battery storage</a> — home and business</li>
        <li><a href="/services/residential/heat-pump-systems">Heat pump hot water</a> — polyvalent systems with COP 7:1</li>
        <li><a href="/services/residential/comfort-conditioning">Hydronic heating and cooling</a> — radiant ceiling panels</li>
        <li><a href="/services/residential/home-automation">Home automation</a> — energy management and smart control</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Research and Development</h2>
      <p>
        We operate a purpose-built research facility with a full-scale TestCell for thermal comfort and energy efficiency testing. This facility allows us to test products under controlled, measurable conditions before they go into homes.
      </p>
      <p>
        Products developed in our facility include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/laboratory/hydronic-ceiling-panels">Hydronic ceiling panels</a> — suspended radiant panels for heating and cooling</li>
        <li><a href="/laboratory/environmental-service-pod">Environmental Service Pod (ESP)</a> — an integrated modular system combining solar, battery, heat pump, and thermal storage</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Service Area</h2>
      <p>
        We're based at 13 Nobility Street, Moolap VIC 3224 — and we service Greater Geelong, Torquay, the Surf Coast, Bellarine Peninsula, Golden Plains, and wider regional Victoria.
      </p>
      <p>
        Because we're local, we're here for the long term. We don't disappear after installation — we're down the road if you need us.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="/services/consultation">Book a free consultation</a> or call us on <a href="tel:0427664827">0427 664 827</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="team-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="team-heading">The Team</h2>

      <div class="team-grid">
        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/DrMarkLuther_clean_transparent.png" alt="Mark B. Luther" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Mark B. Luther</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Director (Arch.D. - Architect)</p>
          <p>Honorary Professor of Deakin University after 27 years of service. He specialises in Architecture Science and Environmental Technology. Inventor of the Environmental Service Pod and the Autonomatic Hydronic Ceiling Panel.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/LincolnLuther_clean_transparent.png" alt="Lincoln B. Luther" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Lincoln B. Luther</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Manager of Sales</p>
          <p>Over 4 years industry experience in the renewables energy sector with a background in Economics, Banking and Finance. He specialises in solar, battery and renewable building services.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/Matthew Ellison_02_clean_transparent.png" alt="Matthew Ellison" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Matthew Ellison</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Manager of Installations</p>
          <p>Senior electrician experienced in Solar PV and Battery installations in commercial and residential projects. Also involved with electrical research and design on the Environmental Service Pod and Hydronic Control.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/HungQDo_clean_transparent.png" alt="Hung Q. Do" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Hung Q. Do</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Research Development</p>
          <p>PhD candidate specialising in hydronic ceiling innovative systems. His research focuses on effective conditioning through hydronic control in commercial buildings.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/placeholder.svg" alt="Pat Sandall" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Pat Sandall</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Head Electrician, A Grade</p>
          <p>A Grade electrician leading EES field installations across solar, battery, and integrated energy systems for residential and commercial projects.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member">
          <img src="/image/photos_team/placeholder.svg" alt="Caleb Nowson" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Caleb Nowson</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Business Development Manager</p>
          <p>Manages business development and client relationships, connecting homeowners and businesses with the right energy solutions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .team-section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .team-heading {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0E2B47;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .team-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .team-member {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .team-member img {
    width: 160px;
    height: 160px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top center;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #fff;
    border: 3px solid #e5e7eb;
    margin: 0 auto 1rem;
    display: block;
  }

  .team-member h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0E2B47;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .team-role {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #2061B7;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .team-member > p:last-child {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .team-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .team-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
